'''Mezweɣ''' neɣ '''Imzuyeɣ''' ([[Izumal n yimtiwgen|Azamul-is]]: <span style="font-size:150%; font-weight:bold">♂</span>) d [[itrikli|amtiweg]] wis 4 deg wuggug (lbeɛdan) ɣef [[tafukt|tfukt]] deg [[Udus anafuk|wudus anafuk]], iga d anarag uffiɣ n deffir n [[tagnit|tegnit]] akken yettwasesmel d [[amtiweg anamur]] yettemcabin i tegnit<ref name="Zubrin1997">{{Tanagit s wedlis |Azwel=The Case for Mars: The Plan to Settle the Red Planet and Why We Must |anafsar=Touchstone |adeg=New York |amezwar1=Robert |aneggar1=Zubrin |amezwar2=Richard |aneggar2=Wagner |azemz=1997 |oclc=489144963 |isbn=978-0-684-83550-1}}</ref>. Isem-is deg [[Tamaziɣt|Tmaziɣt]] yekka-d seg ''[[azeggaɣ|tezweɣ]]'' acku yettbin-d d azeggaɣ deg igenni s usrag n wakal-is d tegnewt-is, Ma d yisem-is [[Talatinit|Alatin]] '(''Mars'') d isem n yellu n umsenɣi ɣer iṛumaniyen, akken daɣen yettwassen s yisem n '''umtiweg azeggaɣ''' deg tlemmast n imusnawen acki [[ini]] n umtiweg-a d azwawaɣ imalen ɣer tezweɣ s usrag n ugedṛur n [[Akṛuksid n wuzzal|ukṛuksid n wuzzal]] yellan s tuget deg tiggi-ines d tignewt-is.<ref>"The Lure of Hematite". Science@NASA. NASA. March 28, 2001. Archived from the original on January 14, 2010. Retrieved December 24, 2009.</ref>

[[Tugna:OSIRIS_Mars_true_color.jpg|thumb|]]

[[Akdu|Akdu-ines]] yettawaṭ ɣer wazal n 6792 km, ayen yegdan azgen n ukdu n tegnit, akken iga d amtiweg ameẓyan wis sin deg wudus anafuk send n [[Merkur]] anda tajumma-ines tla (tesɛa) azal n wezgen n tjumma n tegnit.

Mezweɣ itezzi ɣef tfukt deg [[timezzit|tmezzit]] yaggugin (ibeɛden) fell-as s wazal n 228 km (1,5 n tikkal n westum gar n tegnit d tfukt). [[Amda agafan (mezweɣ)|Amda agafan]] deg ugafa n tuzza iteddel azal n 40% n umtiweg, ayen i d-igellun s usemdu meqqren fell-as.<ref name="مولد تلقائيا38"> Yeager, Ashley (July 19, 2008). "Impact May Have Transformed Mars". ScienceNews.org. Retrieved August 12, 2008.</ref><ref name="Amessiru awurman26"> Sample, Ian (June 26, 2008). "Cataclysmic impact created north-south divide on Mars". London: Science @ guardian.co.uk. Retrieved August 12, 2008.</ref>
Mezweɣ ila (yesɛa) sin n [[ayyur|wayyuren]], amezwar isemis [[Dimus]] (anamek-is d ''[[arameɣ]]'' s [[tutlayt Tagrikt]]) ma d wis sin d [[Fubyus]] (anamek-is d ''[[Tugdi]]''), isin-nsen meẓẓiy-it ur myegdan ara deg talɣa akken izemren ad ilin d [[azunyur|izunyuren]] i d-ildey<ref>{{Cite Web |akala=http://space.about.com/od/mars/a/Mars-Moon-Mystery.htm |Azwel=Mars Moon Mystery |series=Space |amahil=About.com |amezwar=John P. |aneggar=Millis| akala n ufaylu = https://web.archive.org/web/20160722022355/http://space.about.com/od/mars/a/Mars-Moon-Mystery.htm | azemz n ufaylu = 22 yulyu 2016 }}</ref><ref name=adler>{{Aseɣwen asarag |url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/marsconcepts2012/pdf/4337.pdf |title=Use of MRO Optical Navigation Camera to Prepare for Mars Sample Return |conference=Concepts and Approaches for Mars Exploration. June 12–14, 2012. Houston, Texas. |first1=M. |last1=Adler |first2=W. |last2=Owen |first3=J. |last3=Riedel |issue=1679 |at=4337 |date=June 2012 |bibcode=2012LPICo1679.4337A| akala n ufaylu = https://web.archive.org/web/20190608040947/https://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/marsconcepts2012/pdf/4337.pdf | azemz n ufaylu = 8 yunyu 2019 }}</ref> am [[5261 Eureka]]<ref>Yeomans، Donald K.، "5261 Eureka (1990 MB)"، JPL Small-Body Database Browser، NASA، yettwaɣra deg wass n 13 yebrir 2016.</ref>, igan d [[atṛuyan amazwaɣ]].<ref> Trilling, David; Rivking, Andrew; Stansberry, John; Spahr, Timothy; Crudo, Richard; Davies, John (2007). "Albedos and diameters of three Mars Trojan asteroids". Icarus 192 (2): 442–447. arXiv:0709.1921. Bibcode:2007Icar..192..442T. doi:10.1016/j.icarus.2007.08.002. Alsaru yettwaklasen 24 ɣuct 2017 deg tansa n Wayback Machine.</ref>

[[Taẓɣelt]] tajummant tafellayt deg umtiweg-a d tin yettawaṭen alamma d 27° ma d taẓɣelt taddayt -133°, ma d tignut-is d tin igebren seg [[asinuksid n ukaṛbun|usinuksid n ukaṛbun]] d [[Aẓut|unitrujin]] d [[argun|wergun]] d [[irragen n waman|yirragen n waman]] d kracn igazen niden.  Azamul-is asnallun d [[Azamul n Mezweɣ|♂]].

Ussan d [[tasemhuyt|tsemhuyin n useggas]] deg mezweɣ d wid yemrawasen i wayen yellan deg [[tagnit|tegnit]] acku tallit n tuzzya d umili n [[tadɣert n tuzzya|tedɣert n tuzzya]] d tid yettemcabin s waṭas, Dɣa imusnawen ttɣilen d akken amtiweg n mezweɣ yella yeččur d [[aman]] send n 3,8 n imelyaṛen n iseggasen ayen i d-ten-iǧǧan ad brun i teẓri n tilit n tudert deg-s ɣas ma zik-nni, akken illant deg-s [[adrar|idurar]] yugaren wid yellan deg tegnit yakk d isafen yeqquren. Akken i tella deg-s [[taẓrumest|teẓrumest]] tameqqṛant yakk deg wudus anafuk isem-is [[Olympus Mons]] yeddmen isem-a seg [[Adrar n Ulimp|wedrar n ulimpus]],Akken ig yella deg-s [[Valles Marineris|wasif n Marineris]] igan d yiwen seg [[taɣit (tarakalt)|tiɣa]] meqqren yakk deg wudus anafuk.

Asekkud n Mezweɣ s wallen d ayen yefraren (isehlen) s waṭas, [[Azal amaskad|Azal-is amaskad]] yettawaṭ ɣer -2.94, dɣa azal amaskad n [[Yebter]]  d [[tatrit]] d [[ayyur|wayyur]] d [[tafukt|tafukt]] ugaren agla n Mezweɣ<ref name="Amessiru awurman 141"> Mallama, Anthony; Hilton, James L. (October 2018). "Computing apparent planetary magnitudes for The Astronomical Almanac". Astronomy and Computing. 25: 10–24. arXiv:1808.01973. Bibcode:2018A&C....25...10M. doi:10.1016/j.ascom.2018.08.002.</ref>. 

S unect n tezrawt n sin n imusnawen n [[Iwunak Yeddukklen n Temrikt|Marikan]], Mezweɣ yezmer ad yili d [[itrikli|amtiweg]] ur yesmid ara (ur ikemmel ara) gemmu-ines seld mi ig slek seg waṭas n imickaṭen yakk d [[Asmil (tasnallunt)|yesmilen]] d [[aseffud|iseffuden]] d [[tafekka tagnnawt|tfekkiwin tigennawin]] niden i d-illan seg wass mi i d-innulfa wudus anafuk (ayen i d-iglan s temɣer n yimtiwgen akken ma llan), Anecta yessegzaw-d temẓi n ubleɣ n mezweɣ s wassaɣ ɣer [[tagnit|tegnit]] d [[tatrit]], Dɣa sin n imusnawen-a ffɣen-d s ugemmud-a seld n tezrawt taminigt i [[Afaris n werjan|ifuras n werjan imezzerzen]] deg iseffuden

== Iylanen n umtiwen n mezweɣ ==
[[Tugna:MRO-First Image-crop.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Yiwet seg tiwlafin timezwura n mezweɣ s tkamra n [[HiRISE]].]]
Tajumma mezweɣ d tin yugaren amacemma akuẓ n tjumma n [[Tagnit|tegnit]] (28,4% n tjumma n Tagnit),<ref> name="69">Williams, David R. (September 1, 2004). "Mars Fact Sheet". National Space Science Data Center. NASA. Archived from the original on June 12, 2010. Retrieved June 24, 2006.</ref> yerna tineẓẓi n mezweɣ de tin yemgaraden ɣef tneẓẓi n tegnit, anda ableɣ-is isgensis-d  azal n 15% n ubleɣ n tegnit. Ma d takura-ines tegda amraw (1/10) neɣ 11% n tkura n tegnit, ma d taldayt tajummant n mezweɣ tegda 38% s umerwes ɣer teldayt n tegnit, [[adad agnaw|adad agennaw]] deg tjumma n mezweɣ 0,75% n wadad agennaw deg tegnit.

Udem azeggaɣ/ačinay n tjumma n mezweɣ yegla-d yis [[uksyd n wuzzal (III) yakk d ubṛac (ṣṣdid) <ref>Peplow, Mark (May 6, 2004). "How Mars got its rust". Nature. Macmillan Publishers Ltd. Retrieved March 10, 2007.</ref><ref name="a.a10">NASA – Mars in a Minute: Is Mars Really Red? (Transcript)</ref>, ma d initen imezdiyen nniden deg tjumma-ines gan d aras, azegza d urɣan (s ugani ɣef telmas n yimɣuzen yellan.<ref name="a.a10" />

[[Azwu]] n mezweɣ yegber seg 95% n [[asinuksid n ukaṛbun|usinuksid n ukaṛbun]], 3% [[uẓut]], 1,6% [[argun]]  <ref name="a.a68">Chang, Kenneth (November 5, 2015). "Solar Storms Strip Air From Mars, NASA Says". The New York Times. Retrieved November 5, 2015.</ref> d kra n [[uksijin|wuksujin]] d waman.<ref name="a.a67">Staff (November 5, 2015). "VIDEO (51:58) – MAVEN – Measuring Mars' Atmospheric Loss". NASA. Retrieved November 5, 2015.</ref> dɣa deg useggas n 2000 kra n imusnawen ssawṭen ɣer igemmuden i d-iqqaren s tilin n tudert deg mezweɣ deg yizri seld n tmuɣli n tgezmiwin n yiwen n [[aseffud|useffud]] ufant deg [[Antraktika]] yekka-d seg mezweɣ, maca tiẓri ayi mači d tin deg wacu i d-yella usentem ummid.<ref name="a a 145">Northon, Karen (November 5, 2015). "NASA Mission Reveals Speed of Solar Wind Stripping Martian Atmosphere". NASA. Retrieved November 5, 2015.</ref>

Mezweɣ yettumeggez d [[amtiwen anamur]], u tuget n tjumma-ines zeggaɣ-t anagar kra n icamiṭen imsullsen s usrag n wakal-is d yiẓra-ines. Ma d tineẓẓi n adad-is agennaw d tamidrust, tegber s talɣa tagejdant seg usinuksid n ukaṛbun d kra seg yirragen n waman. Anezwu n mezweɣ semmeṭ ugar n tegnit ma d aseggas degs 687 seg wussan n tegnit.<ref name="Wall, Mike 2015">Wall, Mike (November 5, 2015). "Mars Lost Atmosphere to Space as Life Took Hold on Earth". Space.com. Retrieved November 6, 2015.</ref>

